Subject: wifi: ath11k: use IOMMU paging domain allocator

Linux 6.18 no longer exposes iommu_domain_alloc(). Use the current
iommu_paging_domain_alloc() helper when ath11k AHB creates the firmware
IOMMU domain.

Signed-off-by: Igor Kravchenko <igor.kravchenko05@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ahb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ahb.c
@@ -1063,7 +1063,7 @@ static int ath11k_ahb_fw_resources_init(
 
 	ab_ahb->fw.dev = &pdev->dev;
 
-	iommu_dom = iommu_domain_alloc(&platform_bus_type);
+	iommu_dom = iommu_paging_domain_alloc(ab_ahb->fw.dev);
 	if (!iommu_dom) {
 		ath11k_err(ab, "failed to allocate iommu domain\n");
 		ret = -ENOMEM;
